    {
      "id": "283839aa6902285fd8ccd2867923167ef7e866d6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2016-09-30 14:50:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSadly, Andreas, nothing has changed there.  From SLES12:\n#define task_contributes_to_load(task)  \\\n                                ((task->state & TASK_UNINTERRUPTIBLE) != 0 && \\\n                                 (task->flags & PF_FROZEN) == 0)\n\nIn this use case, though, if I'm reading the macro right, we're not sleeping in TASK_INTERRUPTIBLE anyway.  We're actually sleeping in TASK_UNINTERRUPTIBLE, so in this usage, we're contributing to load.\n\nSo this swap is probably harmless...  But I also think it's probably not doing anything...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
